Description:
Ballistics of the Type 73 Universal HEAT-T shot (industrial designation WB122P) for the Type 73, 86 smoothbore anti-tank gun, Type 59 rifled-, and Type 69 smoothbore tank guns. 

Universal denotes compatibility with both rifled and smoothbore armaments. Loads 4.8 kg of propellant charge, including 3.84 kg 13/7 + 0.82 kg 18/1 + 0.14 kg 10/1 Potassium-Rosin. Chambrage is estimated at 1.42.

Type 69 is a smoothbore conversion of the Type 59 tank gun (domestic version of Soviet tank gun D-10), Type 73 employs the same barrel and ammo as Type 69 tank gun, with other parts patterned after the Soviet field gun BS-3. When fired from the Type 69, develops 1010 m/s from 2530 kgf/cm² measured from copper crusher gauge, converts to 277.7 MPa piezoelectric.

When fired from the Type 59 rifled tank gun, velocity and pressure is reduced due to blowpast through rifling.

Performance statistics takes after 1973年式100毫米滑膛反坦克炮《国产火炮手册（说明部分）》. Note that per 1969年式100毫米滑膛坦克炮 lists the same at 1000 m/s. Charge design per 《炮弹火箭弹手册：第二分册 陆军炮弹与火箭弹》.
